# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Client environment variables (Vite)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to .env.local for local overrides.
# In production, set these as build-time env vars on your host.
#
# VITE_API_BASE
#   Absolute base URL of the Node + Express API.
#
#   Required only when the SPA and the API are on DIFFERENT origins.
#   Leave empty when they share an origin (most setups — reverse proxy
#   splits /api and /health to the API, everything else to the static
#   bundle) or for local dev (Vite proxy handles the split).
#
#   Format:  https://api.example.com
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_API_BASE=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD
#   Password for the admin UI gate (client-side only).
#
#   Security model:
#     This value is baked into the compiled JS bundle. It is NOT a real
#     secret — a determined user with DevTools can extract it. This is
#     intentional and acceptable because:
#       (a) The app URL is only shared with trusted colleagues.
#       (b) Tools have no destructive write operations.
#       (c) Real secrets (LLM API keys) live in server-side env vars.
#
#   Set this to any string before deploying.
#   Leave empty → admin login is disabled (admin panel unreachable).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_PUBLIC_TOOLS
#   Comma-separated list of tool IDs visible to anonymous (non-admin)
#   visitors. Source of truth for tool visibility on the landing page.
#
#   Admins (after signing in with VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD) always see ALL tools.
#
#   Valid IDs (must match the registry in shell/LandingPage.jsx):
#     ds-analyser, tech-scope
#
#   Examples:
#     VITE_PUBLIC_TOOLS=                                # nothing public
#     VITE_PUBLIC_TOOLS=tech-scope                      # only Tech Scope
#     VITE_PUBLIC_TOOLS=tech-scope,ds-analyser          # both public
#
#   Changes require a rebuild (Vite inlines env at build time).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
VITE_PUBLIC_TOOLS=
